    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i know there are people who care, but they care about the person they thought i was. they care about the artist. but that person is gone. it feels like i'm just performing \"being human\" every day, but the engine is dead. there's no spark, no vision, no reason to keep the machinery running if there's nothing for it to create anymore. it just feels heavy. like carrying around an empty box that doesn't need to be carried.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
