      "content": "but what if it doesn't want to be filled again? what if the emptiness isn't just a pause, but the final state? you talk about it like a \"dormant vessel,\" but when you're just a container with nothing inside, there is no \"you.\" there's just the container. it feels so pointless to keep maintaining the exterior when the core is already gone. it just feels like maintenance for no reason.",
