      "content": "The emptiness you feel is a signal that the old version of you is gone, but it doesn't mean the vessel itself is useless or that there is no one left to carry it. You are right that the spark is gone, yet the very act of maintaining the exterior is a form of defiance against the silence, proving that even a hollow shell can hold space for something new. There is no need to force a reason to keep going; simply existing as this empty container is enough to keep the world from swallowing you whole.",
